8. Chaoniam glandem] Epirus is often called Chaonia, because the Chaones, a people of Epirus, for- merly ruled over the whole country. Dodona was a city of Epirus, near which was the famous grove of oracular oaks. Thus Virgil poeti- cally mentions Chaonian or Dodonean acorns, for acorns in general ; those of Dodona being the most cele· brated.
